						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, central shrine, Anantēśvarasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 3: 974 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records a gift of 12(1/2) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a perpetual lamp before the deity Chandraśēkhara perumāḷ by Pañchavanmādēvi, the consort of Araiyan Mahimālayaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Parāntaka Muttaraiyaṉ. The shepherd community <hi rend="italic">(maṉṟāḍikkalaṉai)</hi> of the place received the amount and undertook to supply an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee daily for the purpose.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 61.</p>						

						</summary>
